        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): expose fs discovery tools to codex",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add ls/find/grep to the core fs tool catalog and coding tool construction\n- include fs discovery tools in embedded Codex app-server construction\n- update group:fs allow/deny coverage\n- stabilize the slow bundle MCP tools/list timeout assertion under CI shard load\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Codex/OpenClaw app-server coding runs that allow `group:fs` could build `read/write/edit` but not discovery tools, so workspace listing/search fell back to shell approval instead of native `ls/find/grep` tools.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS with the actual `createOpenClawCodingTools` runtime path. The same behavior was also hotpatched into Polytopic production while this upstream PR is pending.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  - `node --import tsx -e \"import { createOpenClawCodingTools } from './src/agents/agent-tools.ts'; const names = createOpenClawCodingTools({ workspaceDir: process.cwd(), config: { tools: { allow: ['group:fs'], deny: ['exec', 'process', 'apply_patch'] } } }).map((tool) => tool.name); console.log(names.join('\\n'));\"`\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n  - Copied console output:\n    ```text\n    [agents/tool-policy] tool policy removed 3 tool(s) via tools.deny: apply_patch, exec, process; matched apply_patch, exec, process\n    [agents/tool-policy] tool policy removed 19 tool(s) via tools.allow: agents_list, create_goal, cron, gateway, get_goal, message, nodes, session_status, sessions_history, sessions_list, sessions_send, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, skill_workshop, subagents, tts, update_goal, web_fetch, web_search\n    read\n    grep\n    find\n    ls\n    edit\n    write\n    ```\n- Observed result after fix: `group:fs` now constructs native `grep`, `find`, and `ls` tools alongside `read/edit/write` while shell/process tools remain denied. Workspace discovery no longer requires falling back to `exec` when only fs tools are approved.\n- What was not tested: Full external-provider model invocation in this PR branch.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: Upstream merge requires an OpenClaw maintainer; Tayoun can update the fork branch and PR but cannot merge upstream. Production Polytopic verification was done via a temporary hotpatch because upstream is still pending.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Before this patch, CI/test expectations and runtime construction exposed `read/write/edit` for fs policy, while `grep/find/ls` were absent from the app-server coding tool construction path.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/tool-catalog.test.ts src/agents/sandbox-explain.test.ts`\n- `TMPDIR=/tmp node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-core.config.ts src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-runtime.test.ts -t \"keeps MCP tools/list responses\"`\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/agent-tools.create-openclaw-coding-tools.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-tool-construction-plan.test.ts`\n\nRegression coverage updated for the coding tool catalog, sandbox `group:fs` expansion, app-server construction allowlists, and slow bundle MCP catalog timing.",
